key_conclusion:
Virtual Insanity is written in the key of D♯ Minor.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 10th most popular key among Minor keys and     the 22nd most popular  among all keys. Minor keys, along with major keys, are a common choice for popular music.  The three most important chords, built off the 1st, 4th and 5th scale degrees are all minor chords (D♯ minor, G♯ minor, and A♯ minor).
